Label: Northeast (Census)
Description: Includes public schools in Connecticut, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, and Vermont.

Label: Midwest (Census)
Description: Includes public schools in Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Michigan, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, Ohio, South Dakota, and Wisconsin.

Label: South (Census)
Description: Includes public schools in Alabama, Arkansas, Delaware, District of Columbia, Florida, Georgia, Kentucky, Louisiana, Maryland, Mississippi, North Carolina, Oklahoma, South Carolina, Tennessee, Texas, Virginia, and West Virginia.

Label: West (Census)
Description: Includes public schools in Alaska, Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, Idaho, Montana, Nevada, New Mexico, Oregon, Utah, Washington, and Wyoming.

Label: District of Columbia
Description: To be used when comparing District of Columbia to states

Label: DoDEA/DDESS
Description: Department of Defense Education Activity/Department of Defense Domestic Dependent Elementary and Secondary Schools

Label: DoDEA/DoDDS
Description: Department of Defense Education Activity/Department of Defense Dependents Schools (overseas)

Label: Large city
Description: Students from public schools in all districts participating and in all large central cities not participating in the urban district assessment. Typically used as a benchmark for urban districts in the way that national public is used for states.

Label: National public
Description: Students from public schools only.  Includes charter schools; excludes Bureau of Indian Education schools and Department of Defense Education Activity schools. To be used when comparing national data to those of states, urban districts, or regions.

Label: National
Description: All students from public and nonpublic schools

Label: Northeast (NAEP)
Description: Use discontinued after 2002.  Includes public schools in Connecticut, Delaware, District of Columbia, Maine, Maryland, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, Vermont, and Virginia (D.C. metropolitan area only).

Label: Southeast (NAEP)
Description: Use discontinued after 2002.  Includes public schools in Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Kentucky, Louisiana, Mississippi, North Carolina, South Carolina, Tennessee, Virginia (outside the D.C. metropolitan area), and West Virginia.

Label: Central (NAEP)
Description: Use discontinued after 2002.  Includes public schools in Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Michigan, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, Ohio, South Dakota, and Wisconsin.

Label: West (NAEP)
Description: Use discontinued after 2002.  Includes public schools in Alaska, Arizona, California, Colorado, Hawaii, Idaho, Montana, Nevada, New Mexico, Oklahoma, Oregon, Texas, Utah, Washington, and Wyoming.

Label: District of Columbia (DCPS)
Description: To be used when comparing District of Columbia to urban districts
